  🧠 The bug[0m[2m is clear: classic race condition in the `transfer` function. When 5 concurrent transfers happen:
     
     1. All 5 tasks read Alice[0m[2m's balance ($100) before any write happens
     2. All 5 tasks think they can deduct $20
     3. Each[0m[2m writes $80, so instead of losing $100 total (5 ×[0m[2m $20), money gets lost
     
     The fix needs to make the read-check-write operation atomic.[0m[2m I can use a lock in the database class to ensure only one transfer operates at a time.
